  <h2>Hyperlinks</h2>
  <p>
    Hyperlinks can link to other resources, such as links, websites, media, or
    other content within the same page. In the following example, the link would
    navigate the user to page.html within the same folder/directory.
  </p>

  <Code
    code={`<a href="page.html">Page</a>
<a href="./page.html">Page</a>`}
    lang="html"
  />

  <p>
    Hyperlinks can also link to external websites. The example below links to
    HACC's website and contains the attribute _target (in this case telling the
    link to open in a new tab) and title (which displays a tooltip when the user
    hovers over the link):
  </p>
  <Code
    code={`<a href="https://www.hacc.edu" target="_blank" title="HACC">HACC</a>`}
    lang="html"
  />

